        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"276114\">Chad Nester</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229136-theory.3A-category.20theory/topic/The.20relative.2Fmap.20perspective.2Fphilosophy/near/247586221\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I've just noticed that in the single-sorted version the identity maps are precisely the fixed points of the source (equivalently, target) function. Neat!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>This is 1.13 in Freyd and Scedrov's <em>Categories, Allegories</em>, if you ever want a reference.</p>",
